leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|narrowing_1|1|When movement gets ahead of the whole picture|Results can narrow when urgency pulls attention towards the next decision before the wider conditions are clear. The work may gain movement, but it can also skip the structure, future reason, or trust needed for follow-through to hold.|people|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::narrowing_1
leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|narrowing_2|2|When Results and Process take most of the space|Results and Process can narrow together when the combination of decision, ownership, and follow-through with sequence, standards, and dependable handover answers the first questions too quickly. The pattern may look productive, but it can leave less room for a stronger future frame and reason for the work or clearer communication, inclusion, and relational judgement until the work is harder to adjust.|vision|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::narrowing_2
leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|narrowing_3|3|Before People is added|Vision can add range before People is brought in deliberately, but the pattern may still narrow if People is left until later. The likely miss is progress that looks organised from the outside while commitment, confidence, or shared understanding needs more attention, especially when Results and Process already feel convincing.|people|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::narrowing_3
